				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Not a matter of opinion imo: An uniformed groundsperson. The point of the An/A distinction is to separate the vowel sounds when read out loud, it depends entirely on the leading vowel of the immediately following word.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

