				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Yeh, clearly I&#8217;m a &#8220;if it doesn&#8217;t sound like a vowel&#8221; person <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> I also found <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_articles#Discrimination_between_a_and_an" rel="nofollow">this discussion of the choice between a/an</a> on Wikipedia on the whole topic. It talks about &#8220;a&#8221; and &#8220;an&#8221; being used based on the sound of the word, rather than how it is spelled.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

