									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I have to agree with Parfles and cbraz, the &#8220;u&#8221; sound here actually functions more like a consonant (&#8220;yuniformed&#8221;) than a vowel, and therefore doesn&#8217;t need &#8220;an&#8221;. The obverse example is &#8220;an hour&#8221;, which is a consonant that acts like a vowel.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

